{
  "texts": [
    "In MT, the decoder is responsible, as it were, for generating wellformed text in the target language that represents the meaning of the text in the source language, as depicted by the encoder.",
    "Virtually all current models in the field of generative AI (including, for instance, image or music generation over and above the most important field of natural language generation) follow this basic pattern of using ever increasing numbers of ever larger decoder blocks from the transformer.",
    "Currently, it is likely that the most potent NLG-model is called GPT-4.",
    "Even more than GPT-3.5-turbo, GPT-4 is shielded against any proper scientific investigation: it is not known what data it was trained on, what the specific training method was, what hardware was used, whether there are any modifications to the GPT-architecture, etc.",
    "(hence it is also only likely the most potent NLG-model)."
  ]
}